TITLE: Nike posts first earnings miss in three years as lower margins hit sports apparel giant
SUMMARY: Nike missed on earnings for the first time in three years after promotions and freight costs pressured the sneaker giant's margins.

TITLE: Walgreens slashes earnings guidance due to lower consumer spending, drop in Covid care demand
SUMMARY: CEO Rosalind Brewer said Walgreens will increase its cost-cutting program to $4.1 billion and take action to increase profitability in the health-care segment.

TITLE: Olive Garden parent earnings beat estimates, fueled by strong LongHorn Steakhouse sales
SUMMARY: Darden's Olive Garden had a weaker-than-expected quarter, but LongHorn Steakhouse reported strong same-store sales growth.

TITLE: Oracle beats on top and bottom lines as cloud revenue jumps
SUMMARY: Oracle's cloud infrastructure revenue growth accelerated in the fiscal fourth quarter, and the company sees revenue faster growth than expected.

TITLE: DocuSign shares rise on earnings beat and strong guidance
SUMMARY: In DocuSign's fiscal quarter ended April 30, revenue jumped 12% year-over-year to $661.4 million, beating analyst estimates of $642 million.

TITLE: Planet stock drops 25% after satellite data venture lowers annual revenue guidance
SUMMARY: Planet, a satellite-imagery and data-analysis company, lowered its annual revenue guidance after reporting first-quarter results Thursday.

TITLE: GitLab shares rocket 31% as software vendor boosts forecast, announces generative A.I. plans
SUMMARY: GitLab beat on the top and bottom lines and increased its full-year guidance after raising the price of its premium subscription.

TITLE: Lululemon shares surge after reporting 24% sales growth, raising full-year guidance
SUMMARY: Lululemon reported healthy first-quarter profits that beat Wall Street's estimates.

TITLE: MongoDB shares jump more than 20% after database company beats expectations and raises guidance
SUMMARY: MongoDB flagged continued scrutiny over technology spending, but acquired more clients than analysts had expected during the quarter ending April 30.

TITLE: Macy’s slashes its full-year outlook even as earnings beat
SUMMARY: Macy's gave a lower sales and earnings forecast for the year as it said discretionary spending slowed in March.

TITLE: Salesforce raises guidance but sees pressure as customers back away from big consulting deals
SUMMARY: Salesforce raised its full-year guidance and reported an earnings and revenue beat, but capital costs were higher than expected.

TITLE: CrowdStrike shares tumble as revenue shows signs of slowing
SUMMARY: CrowdStrike reported first-quarter results for its fiscal 2024 year, beating on the top and bottom lines, as China-related cyber concerns mount.

TITLE: Chewy shares surge after earnings beat on top and bottom lines
SUMMARY: Chewy shares surged in extended trading after the company beat earnings estimates on the top and bottom lines.

TITLE: Nordstrom tops Wall Street's first-quarter sales expectations, even as shoppers spend less
SUMMARY: The high-end department store reaffirmed its full-year outlook and posted a surprise profit on an adjusted basis.

TITLE: Advance Auto Parts shares plummet 35% after dismal results, cuts to outlook and dividend
SUMMARY: The auto parts supplier blamed its Q1 results on higher-than-expected costs, inflationary pressure, supply chain problems and lower, unfavorable product mix.

TITLE: British digital bank Monzo hits monthly profitability for the first time after spike in lending
SUMMARY: Monzo's bump in revenues was driven by a spike in lending activity, with net interest income increasing 382% to £164.2 million.

TITLE: Fintech firm Klarna halves net loss in first quarter as it races toward profitability
SUMMARY: The results show that Klarna is making "significant strides" toward profitability on a monthly basis by the second half of 2023, the firm said.

TITLE: Gap shares soar after retailer reports big improvement in margins
SUMMARY: Apparel retailer Gap reported another quarter of net losses and sale dips across its four brands but did manage to significantly improve its margins.

TITLE: Best Buy shares rise on earnings beat, even as CEO says shoppers are showing 'recessionary behaviors'
SUMMARY: Best Buy shares rose, but the retailer expects weaker spending on consumer electronics the rest of the year.

TITLE: Nvidia shares spike 26% on huge forecast beat driven by A.I. chip demand
SUMMARY: Nvidia is the top provider of advanced GPU chips for artificial intelligence.

TITLE: Snowflake shares plunge 12% on guidance miss, acquisition of search startup Neeva
SUMMARY: Snowflake beat on the top and bottom lines for the fiscal first quarter, but it gave product revenue guidance that missed consensus estimates.

TITLE: American Eagle Outfitters shares sink as retailer lowers forecast
SUMMARY: The mall-based retailer's results diverged from Abercrombie & Fitch's earlier in the day.

TITLE: Abercrombie & Fitch surges more than 30% after reporting surprise profit
SUMMARY: Mall apparel retailer Abercrombie & Fitch surprised investors with a fiscal first-quarter profit, sending shares surging.

TITLE: Chinese Tesla rival shares dive 11% after it forecasts a plunge in car deliveries
SUMMARY: Xpeng has been hurt by a tough macroeconomic situation in China as well as rising competition from Tesla, BYD and electric car startups.

TITLE: Kohl's shares jump as retailer reports a surprise profit
SUMMARY: Kohl's unexpectedly posted a profit and reaffirmed its full-year guidance.

TITLE: Shares of Urban Outfitters spike after fiscal first-quarter earnings beat
SUMMARY: Shares of Urban Outfitters spiked about 8% after the company reported fiscal first-quarter earnings that beat on the top and bottom lines.

TITLE: Lowe's cuts full-year sales forecast, even as it tops earnings and revenue estimates
SUMMARY: Lowe's beat first-quarter earnings expectations but lowered its full-year sales outlook.

TITLE: Ryanair reports bumper profit on 'favorable' fuel hedges, sees major industry consolidation
SUMMARY: Ryanair CEO Michael O'Leary said the airline's "industry leading" fuel hedging contributed significantly to its full-year profit.

TITLE: Foot Locker's 27% plunge, guidance cut may signal trouble ahead for other retailers
SUMMARY: Foot Locker shares plunged more than 27% on Friday after a slowdown in consumer spending led to a drop in sales and weak guidance.

TITLE: Bath & Body Works' stock surges after it raises guidance, beats on earnings
SUMMARY: Bath & Body Works saw year-over-year declines in sales and profits in its fiscal first quarter, but its stock surged after it raised its guidance for the year.
